snippet.textDisplay: I think I’ve got a really cool and logical reason why they would make such a similar name for a new Xbox consul. So you know the reason why Sony keeps on bringing numerical names such as PlayStation 3, PlayStation 4, PlayStation 4 pro, PlayStation 5 is because the main seller for the name is the brand PlayStation. So they wouldn’t be able to call it butterfly because PlayStation has to be part of the name. I used to think, and I still do, that it should’ve been Sony PlayStation and not just PlayStation. But apparently Sony is a far lesser part of a name. Now for the Xbox, the word One was probably dependent on their One Drive and One note apps. But after releasing One X and having a bunch of X’s in the name such as Xbox one X, now they have to stick to this idea of keeping all of those x’sas part of a console name. Also, if the original Xbox was named after direct X in windows, Siries X is named after the X cloud, I agree with that one.
snippet.textOriginal: I think I’ve got a really cool and logical reason why they would make such a similar name for a new Xbox consul. So you know the reason why Sony keeps on bringing numerical names such as PlayStation 3, PlayStation 4, PlayStation 4 pro, PlayStation 5 is because the main seller for the name is the brand PlayStation. So they wouldn’t be able to call it butterfly because PlayStation has to be part of the name. I used to think, and I still do, that it should’ve been Sony PlayStation and not just PlayStation. But apparently Sony is a far lesser part of a name. Now for the Xbox, the word One was probably dependent on their One Drive and One note apps. snippet.textDisplay: i hate consoles. i hope this doesnt negatively affect pc's. consoles should just become pc's. mine did. i moved from xbox 360 to pc years ago. still plugged into my tv. still a very similar thing. just much much much more veratile. and until now far far far more powerful. but this new console threatens that... and they will never make consoles pc, because they dont want you to have that much freedom on your device. walled off garden software is how they limit you and charge you money for every little thing they can. i hate it. that lack of freedom. i understand its how big business works. but its all wrong. pc is amazing, steam is amazing. i will never buy a console. hopefully these better consoles just bring in an era of better pc's/ gpu's cpu's and pc games etc. also, wtf micrisoft, why no vr? i have YOUR vr on my pc, it was affordable and its an amazing experience. you could easily have outdone sony's terrible vr implementation. i just dont get it. vr is bloody brilliant. i can barely get excited about 2d games anymore, but vr is always exciting.
